Usage: clonePtnObj [-help] [-checkOnly] [-objs {all busGuides specialWires}]
                   [-redo] [-refHinsts <list of hinst names>]
                   [-skipCreateNewPartitionPorts] [-sync]
                   [-targetHinsts <list of hinst names>] [-undo]

-help                                # Prints out the command usage
-checkOnly                           # Checks if master and clone partitions
                                     # are out of sync or not (bool, optional)
-objs {all busGuides specialWires}   # Specifies properties which are required
                                     # to be synced (enum_list, optional)
-redo                                # makes the changes done to busGuide again
                                     # and brings user to next sync state
                                     # (bool, optional)
-refHinsts <list of hinst names>     # Specifies name of the hinsts from whom
                                     # objects will be copied to target_hinsts
                                     # (string, optional)
-skipCreateNewPartitionPorts         # specifies to skip create new partition
                                     # ports during sync-up for top-level net
                                     # passing over case (bool, optional)
-sync                                # specifies if syncing of busGuide is
                                     # required (bool, optional)
-targetHinsts <list of hinst names>  # Specifies name of hinsts to whome obj is
                                     # copied from ref hinst (string, optional)
-undo                                # reverts the changes done to busGuide and
                                     # brings user back to last sync state
                                     # (bool, optional)